, Stupid: Why Everything in Medicine Is Connected</a>" in volume 5, e71.</div><div style="border-top: 1px solid rgb(102, 102, 153); margin: 5px 10% 3px;"></div><div>This article has been <a href="/pmc/articles/PMC2270306/citedby/">cited by</a> other articles in PMC.</div></div></div></div><div class="sec"></div><div id="ass-data" class="tsec fm-sec whole_rhythm" data-section="Featured_PMC_Datacitation"><h2>Associated Data</h2><dl data-count="10" class="box-data-suppmats whole_rhythm no_bottom_margin"><dt><a href="#" rid="data-suppmats" data-ga-action="click_feat_toggler" data-ga-label="Supplementary Materials" class="pmctoggle">Supplementary Materials</a></dt><dd id="data-suppmats" style="display: none;"><div class="half_rhythm"><div class="caption half_rhythm no_bottom_margin"><strong>Figure S1: </strong>Histogram of Number of Reported Contacts by Country (7.7 KB PDF)</div><div><a href="/pmc/articles/PMC2270306/bin/pmed.0050074.sg001.pdf" data-ga-action="click_feat_suppl">pmed.0050074.sg001.pdf</a><span style="color:gray"> (7.7K)</span></div><div class="small guid">GUID:\xc2\xa02EC4F139-BB6E-43F6-8C9F-F8E1B49B8F14</div></div><div class="half_rhythm"><div class="caption half_rhythm no_bottom_margin"><strong>Figure S2: </strong>The Proportion of Contacts That Involved Physical Contact, by (a) Duration, (b) Frequency, (c) Location of Contact; and (d) Correlation between Duration and Frequency of Contact Contacts were weighted by country-specific sampling weights in BE (A), DE (B), FI (C), GB (D), IT (E), LU (F), NL (G), and PL (H).<p>(84 KB DOC)</p></div><div><a href="/pmc/articles/PMC2270306/bin/pmed.0050074.sg002.doc" data-ga-action="click_feat_suppl">pmed.0050074.sg002.doc</a><span style="color:gray"> (84K)</span></div><div class="small guid">GUID:\xc2\xa0C422A3A6-5BE8-4B6F-9DB0-4C64A3A7FBED</div></div><div class="half_rhythm"><div class="caption half_rhythm no_bottom_margin"><strong>Figure S3: </strong>Smoothed Weighted Contact Matrices for Each Country Based on R