s. NH conducted the data mining and surface smoothing. JW and JH conducted the epidemic modelling. All authors approved the final manuscript.</p></div><p class="fn sec" id="n101"><p id="__p88" class="p p-first-last"><strong>Funding:</strong> This study formed part of POLYMOD, a European Commission project funded within the Sixth Framework Programme, Contract number: SSP22-CT-2004&#x02013;502084. The funders had no role in study design, data collection and analysis, decision to publish, or preparation of the manuscript.</p></p><p class="fn sec" id="n102"> <p id="__p89" class="p p-first-last"><strong>Competing Interests:</strong> The authors have declared that no competing interests exist.</p></p></div></div><div id="idm139826161414992" class="tsec sec"><h2 class="head no_bottom_margin" id="idm139826161414992title">References</h2><div class="ref-list-sec sec" id="reference-list"><ul class="back-ref-list" style="list-style-type:decimal;"><li id="pmed-0050074-b001"><span class="citation">Longini IM, Jr., Nizam A, Xu S, Ungchusak K, Hanshaoworakul W, et al.  Containing pandemic influenza at the source. <span><span class="ref-journal">Science. </span>2005;<span class="ref-vol">309</span>:1083\xe2\x80\x931087.</span> [<a href="/pubmed/16079251" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=pubmed&amp;article-id=2270306&amp;issue-id=162285&amp;journal-id=277&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Entrez%7CPubMed%7CRecord">PubMed</a>] <span class="nowrap">[<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?journal=Science&amp;title=Containing+pandemic+influenza+at+the+source&amp;author=IM+Longini&amp;author=A+Nizam&amp;author=S+Xu&amp;author=K+Ungchusak&amp;author=W+Hanshaoworakul&amp;volume=309&amp;publication_year=2005&amp;pages=1083-1087&amp;pmid=16079251&amp;" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=other&amp;article-id=2270306&amp;issue-id=162285&amp;journal-id=277&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Content%20Provider%7CLink%7CGoogle%20Scholar">Google Scholar</a>]</span></span></li><li id="pme